    "explanation": "Diagram 1 presents a more high-level, layered architecture for a CGI proxy system. It encompasses broader components such as web clients, app clients, business servers, and developers, separated into layers like Access Layer, Proxy Layer, CGI Portal, Support Platform and Task Scheduler.  It also includes specific functional components, like Logging, Appkey Validation, and others. Diagram 2 focuses more specifically on the internal workings of an HTTP proxy system and it details interactions between Test Modules, a Proxy Server, request/response handlers, exception handlers, and configuration files. It shows the internal flow and filtering logic using Netty Framework and custom Filters. \n\nSimilarities exist in the presence of a Proxy component in both diagrams. Though the specifics differ, both diagrams illustrate the concept of a proxy. Both diagrams show the usage of filters. The diagrams are significantly different in scope and detail. Diagram 1 presents the architecture on a higher level while Diagram 2 focuses on the inner components of a proxy system.\n\nDiagram 2 provides more details and a clear flow of actions between components so it may be judged as of higher quality so it can be rated as 7 as it provides details but does not explain the relation to the real world while Diagram 1 has a more comprehensive set of components to use but is not clearly structured rated at a score of 5."
